Class OrderedPairIterator<T>

  utilMDE.OrderedPairIterator<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.util.Iterator<Pair<T,T>>
public class OrderedPairIterator<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<Pair<T,T>>

Given two sequences/iterators/whatever, this class returns a new sequence/iterator/whatever which pairs the matching elements of the inputs, according to their respective sort orders.

In some cases this is just the right abstraction. But in some cases it's appropriate to use set intersection/difference instead.
